[[2019冠状病毒病英国疫情|受2019冠状病毒病疫情期间的大型集会限制规定]]影响，丧礼出席人数限制在30人<ref name="BBC-service" />，扶灵者和神职人员等工作人员除外<ref>{{cite web |title=COVID-19: guidance for arranging or attending a funeral during the coronavirus pandemic |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/covid-19-guidance-for-managing-a-funeral-during-the-coronavirus-pandemic/covid-19-guidance-for-managing-a-funeral-during-the-coronavirus-pandemic |website=GOV.UK |access-date=2021-04-11 |language=en |date=2021-01-22 |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417165008/https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/covid-19-guidance-for-managing-a-funeral-during-the-coronavirus-pandemic/covid-19-guidance-for-managing-a-funeral-during-the-coronavirus-pandemic |dead-url=no }}</ref>。因此，只有王室成员和少数亲戚参加了教堂内的仪式<ref name="ITV-service" />。仪式期间女王单独坐<ref name="Sky-Alone"/>。出席的家人保持两米间隔，全程佩戴口罩，不唱歌<ref>{{cite web|last=Rodger|first=James|date=2021-04-14|title=Prince Philip's funeral rules in full – Queen sits alone and singing ban|url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/news/midlands-news/prince-philips-funeral-rules-full-20381669|access-date=2021-04-15|website=Birmingham Live|archive-date=2021-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416211001/https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/news/midlands-news/prince-philips-funeral-rules-full-20381669|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

